'Space Jam 2' a go, LeBron James to starTue, 03 May 2016 1:10 PM Share
Your Email
US basketball superstar LeBron James during his time with the Cleveland Cavaliers. Credit: AFPJustin Lin is reportedly in early negotiations to direct a sequel to the original basketball-themed live action/animation mash up film Space Jam.
Lin is hot property at the moment. As well as his connection with the Fast and Furious franchise, he is directing the third instalment of Star Trek.
According to The Wrap, Lin is also looking to helm Space Jam 2 with LeBron James in the starring role.
The original film, released in 1996 stared Michael Jordan and featured a host of cameos from NBA all-stars including Patrick Ewing and Charles Barkley alongside Warner Brothers biggest animated stars such as Bugs Bunny and Daffy Duck.
Space Jam 2 could hit cinemas as early as 2017.
AFP-Relaxnews
